{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm going to read a few strips."},{"time":5000,"text":"These are, most of these are"},{"time":7000,"text":"from a monthly page I do"},{"time":9000,"text":"in and architecture and design magazine"},{"time":12000,"text":"called Metropolis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":14000,"text":"And the first story is called"},{"time":16000,"text":"\"The Faulty Switch.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":18000,"text":"Another beautifully designed new building"},{"time":22000,"text":"ruined by the sound of a common wall light switch."},{"time":27000,"text":"It's fine during the day"},{"time":29000,"text":"when the main rooms are flooded with sunlight."},{"time":33000,"text":"But at dusk"},{"time":35000,"text":"everything changes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37000,"text":"The architect spent hundreds of hours"},{"time":40000,"text":"designing the burnished brass switchplates"},{"time":44000,"text":"for his new office tower."},{"time":47000,"text":"And then left it to a contractor"},{"time":49000,"text":"to install these 79-cent switches behind them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":54000,"text":"We know instinctively where to reach"},{"time":57000,"text":"when we enter a dark room."},{"time":59000,"text":"We automatically throw the little nub of plastic upward."},{"time":63000,"text":"But the sound we are greeted with,"},{"time":66000,"text":"as the room is bathed in the simulated glow"},{"time":69000,"text":"of late-afternoon light,"},{"time":72000,"text":"recalls to mind"},{"time":74000,"text":"a dirty men's room"},{"time":76000,"text":"in the rear of a Greek coffee shop."},{"time":79000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":81000,"text":"This sound colors our first impression of any room;"},{"time":85000,"text":"it can't be helped."},{"time":87000,"text":"But where does this sound,"},{"time":89000,"text":"commonly described as a click, come from?"},{"time":93000,"text":"Is it simply the byproduct of a"},{"time":96000,"text":"crude mechanical action?"},{"time":98000,"text":"Or is it an imitation"},{"time":100000,"text":"of one half the set of sounds we make"},{"time":103000,"text":"to express disappointment?"},{"time":106000,"text":"The often dental consonant"},{"time":109000,"text":"of no Indo-European language."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112000,"text":"Or is it the amplified sound"},{"time":114000,"text":"of a synapse firing"},{"time":116000,"text":"in the brain of a cockroach?"},{"time":119000,"text":"In the 1950s they tried their best"},{"time":123000,"text":"to muffle this sound"},{"time":125000,"text":"with mercury switches"},{"time":127000,"text":"and silent knob controls."}]},{"cues":[{"time":130000,"text":"But today these improvements"},{"time":133000,"text":"seem somehow inauthentic."},{"time":136000,"text":"The click is the modern"},{"time":138000,"text":"triumphal clarion"},{"time":140000,"text":"proceeding us through life,"},{"time":143000,"text":"announcing our entry into every lightless room."}]},{"cues":[{"time":147000,"text":"The sound made flicking a wall switch off"},{"time":151000,"text":"is of a completely different nature."},{"time":154000,"text":"It has a deep melancholy ring."},{"time":158000,"text":"Children don't like it."},{"time":161000,"text":"It's why they leave lights on around the house. (Laughter)"},{"time":165000,"text":"Adults find it comforting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":167000,"text":"But wouldn't it be an easy matter"},{"time":169000,"text":"to wire a wall switch"},{"time":172000,"text":"so that it triggers the muted horn of a steam ship?"},{"time":176000,"text":"Or the recorded crowing of a rooster?"},{"time":181000,"text":"Or the distant peel of thunder?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":185000,"text":"Thomas Edison went through"},{"time":187000,"text":"thousands of unlikely substances"},{"time":190000,"text":"before he came upon the right one"},{"time":192000,"text":"for the filament of his electric light bulb."},{"time":197000,"text":"Why have we settled so quickly"},{"time":199000,"text":"for the sound of its switch?"},{"time":202000,"text":"That's the end of that."},{"time":204000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":207000,"text":"The next story is called"},{"time":210000,"text":"\"In Praise of the Taxpayer.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":213000,"text":"That so many of the city's most venerable taxpayers"},{"time":217000,"text":"have survived yet another commercial building boom,"},{"time":222000,"text":"is cause for celebration."}]},{"cues":[{"time":224000,"text":"These one or two story structures,"},{"time":228000,"text":"designed to yield only enough income"},{"time":231000,"text":"to cover the taxes on the land"},{"time":233000,"text":"on which they stand,"},{"time":235000,"text":"were not meant to be permanent buildings."},{"time":239000,"text":"Yet for one reason or another"},{"time":241000,"text":"they have confounded the efforts of developers"},{"time":245000,"text":"to be combined into lots"},{"time":247000,"text":"suitable for high-rise construction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":252000,"text":"Although they make no claim to architectural beauty,"},{"time":256000,"text":"they are, in their perfect temporariness,"},{"time":259000,"text":"a delightful alternative"},{"time":262000,"text":"to the large-scale structures"},{"time":264000,"text":"that might someday take their place."},{"time":268000,"text":"The most perfect examples"},{"time":271000,"text":"occupy corner lots."},{"time":274000,"text":"They offer a pleasant respite"},{"time":276000,"text":"from the high-density development around them."},{"time":279000,"text":"A break of light and air,"},{"time":282000,"text":"an architectural biding of time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285000,"text":"So buried in signage"},{"time":287000,"text":"are these structures,"},{"time":289000,"text":"that it often takes a moment"},{"time":291000,"text":"to distinguish the modern"},{"time":293000,"text":"specially constructed taxpayer"},{"time":296000,"text":"from its neighbor:"},{"time":298000,"text":"the small commercial building"},{"time":301000,"text":"from an earlier century,"},{"time":303000,"text":"whose upper floors have been sealed,"},{"time":306000,"text":"and whose groundfloor space"},{"time":308000,"text":"now functions as a taxpayer."},{"time":312000,"text":"The few surfaces not covered by signs"},{"time":315000,"text":"are often clad in a distinctive, dark"},{"time":318000,"text":"green-gray, striated aluminum siding."},{"time":323000,"text":"Take-out sandwich shops,"},{"time":325000,"text":"film processing drop-offs,"},{"time":328000,"text":"peep-shows and necktie stores."}]},{"cues":[{"time":331000,"text":"Now these provisional structures have,"},{"time":334000,"text":"in some cases,"},{"time":336000,"text":"remained standing"},{"time":338000,"text":"for the better part of a human lifetime."},{"time":342000,"text":"The temporary building"},{"time":344000,"text":"is a triumph of modern industrial organization,"},{"time":348000,"text":"a healthy sublimation"},{"time":350000,"text":"of the urge to build,"},{"time":353000,"text":"and proof that not every"},{"time":355000,"text":"architectural idea"},{"time":357000,"text":"need be set in stone."},{"time":361000,"text":"That's the end."},{"time":363000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":365000,"text":"And the next story is called, \"On the Human Lap.\""},{"time":368000,"text":"For the ancient Egyptians"},{"time":371000,"text":"the lap was a platform"},{"time":373000,"text":"upon which to place"},{"time":375000,"text":"the earthly possessions of the dead --"},{"time":378000,"text":"30 cubits from foot to knee."}]},{"cues":[{"time":381000,"text":"It was not until the 14th century"},{"time":384000,"text":"that an Italian painter"},{"time":386000,"text":"recognized the lap"},{"time":388000,"text":"as a Grecian temple,"},{"time":390000,"text":"upholstered in flesh and cloth."},{"time":394000,"text":"Over the next 200 years"},{"time":397000,"text":"we see the infant Christ"},{"time":399000,"text":"go from a sitting to a standing position"},{"time":402000,"text":"on the Virgin's lap,"},{"time":404000,"text":"and then back again."},{"time":406000,"text":"Every child recapitulates this ascension,"},{"time":410000,"text":"straddling one or both legs,"},{"time":413000,"text":"sitting sideways,"},{"time":415000,"text":"or leaning against the body."}]},{"cues":[{"time":418000,"text":"From there, to the modern ventriloquist's dummy,"},{"time":422000,"text":"is but a brief moment in history."},{"time":425000,"text":"You were late for school again this morning."},{"time":428000,"text":"The ventriloquist must first make us believe"},{"time":432000,"text":"that a small boy is sitting on his lap."},{"time":436000,"text":"The illusion of speech follows incidentally."},{"time":439000,"text":"What have you got to say for yourself, Jimmy?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":443000,"text":"As adults we admire the lap"},{"time":446000,"text":"from a nostalgic distance."},{"time":450000,"text":"We have fading memories"},{"time":452000,"text":"of that provisional temple,"},{"time":454000,"text":"erected each time an adult sat down."},{"time":458000,"text":"On a crowded bus there was always a lap to sit on."},{"time":463000,"text":"It is children and teenage girls"},{"time":466000,"text":"who are most keenly aware"},{"time":468000,"text":"of its architectural beauty."},{"time":472000,"text":"They understand the structural integrity"},{"time":475000,"text":"of a deep avuncular lap,"},{"time":478000,"text":"as compared to the shaky arrangement"},{"time":481000,"text":"of a neurotic niece in high heels."}]},{"cues":[{"time":486000,"text":"The relationship between the lap and its owner"},{"time":490000,"text":"is direct and intimate."},{"time":493000,"text":"I envision a 36-story,"},{"time":495000,"text":"450-unit residential high-rise --"},{"time":500000,"text":"a reason to consider the mental health"},{"time":503000,"text":"of any architect before granting"},{"time":505000,"text":"an important commission."},{"time":508000,"text":"The bathrooms and kitchens will,"},{"time":510000,"text":"of course, have no windows."},{"time":513000,"text":"The lap of luxury"},{"time":516000,"text":"is an architectural construct of childhood,"},{"time":520000,"text":"which we seek, in vain,"},{"time":522000,"text":"as adults, to employ."},{"time":525000,"text":"That's the end."},{"time":527000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":530000,"text":"The next story is called \"The Haverpiece Collection\""},{"time":533000,"text":"A nondescript warehouse,"},{"time":536000,"text":"visible for a moment"},{"time":538000,"text":"from the northbound lanes of the Prykushko Expressway,"},{"time":543000,"text":"serves as the temporary resting place"},{"time":547000,"text":"for the Haverpiece collection"},{"time":550000,"text":"of European dried fruit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":554000,"text":"The profound convolutions"},{"time":556000,"text":"on the surface of a dried cherry."},{"time":559000,"text":"The foreboding sheen of an extra-large date."}]},{"cues":[{"time":564000,"text":"Do you remember wandering as a child"},{"time":567000,"text":"through those dark wooden"},{"time":569000,"text":"storefront galleries?"},{"time":571000,"text":"Where everything was displayed"},{"time":573000,"text":"in poorly labeled roach-proof bins."}]},{"cues":[{"time":578000,"text":"Pears dried in the form"},{"time":580000,"text":"of genital organs."},{"time":583000,"text":"Apricot halves"},{"time":585000,"text":"like the ears of cherubim."}]},{"cues":[{"time":587000,"text":"In 1962 the unsold stock"},{"time":592000,"text":"was purchased by Maurice Haverpiece,"},{"time":595000,"text":"a wealthy prune juice bottler,"},{"time":597000,"text":"and consolidated to form the core collection."},{"time":602000,"text":"As an art form it lies somewhere between"},{"time":605000,"text":"still-life painting and plumbing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":609000,"text":"Upon his death in 1967,"},{"time":613000,"text":"a quarter of the items were sold off for compote"},{"time":617000,"text":"to a high-class hotel restaurant."},{"time":620000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":621000,"text":"Unsuspecting guests were served"},{"time":624000,"text":"stewed turn-of-the-century"},{"time":626000,"text":"Turkish figs for breakfast."},{"time":629000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":630000,"text":"The rest of the collection remains here,"},{"time":633000,"text":"stored in plain brown paper bags"},{"time":637000,"text":"until funds can be raised"},{"time":640000,"text":"to build a permanent museum"},{"time":642000,"text":"and study center."}]},{"cues":[{"time":644000,"text":"A shoe made of apricot leather"},{"time":647000,"text":"for the daughter of a czar."}]},{"cues":[{"time":650000,"text":"That's the end. Thank you."},{"time":653000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}